    "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR introduces atomic reduction operations (AtomicMax, AtomicMin) and enhances the existing atomic add functionality with automatic vectorization support and code architecture improvements.\n\n### Key Changes\n\n- **New Atomic Reduction Operations**: Added `T.atomic_max` and `T.atomic_min` for both element-wise and tile-region-based operations\n- **Atomic Add Vectorization**: Automatic vectorization of `atomic_add_elem_op` to `atomic_addx2_elem_op` (for float16/bfloat16) or `atomic_addx4_elem_op` (for float32 on SM>=90)\n- **Code Refactoring**: Refactored `AtomicAddNode` to inherit from `AtomicOpBaseNode<T>` using CRTP pattern, reducing code duplication\n- **Return Previous Value**: Support for `return_prev=True` parameter to retrieve the previous value in atomic operations\n- **Naming Consistency**: Fixed naming convention for atomic ops with return value (`atomic_add_ret_elem_op`, `atomic_max_ret_elem_op`, `atomic_min_ret_elem_op`)\n\n### New APIs\n\n```python\n# Atomic Max - element-wise\nT.atomic_max(dst[i, j], value)\n\n# Atomic Max - tile-region based\nT.atomic_max(dst_tensor, src_tensor)\n\n# Atomic Min - element-wise\nT.atomic_min(dst[i, j], value)\n\n# Atomic Min - tile-region based  \nT.atomic_min(dst_tensor, src_tensor)\n\n# Atomic Add with return previous value\nold_val = T.atomic_add(dst[i, j], value, return_prev=True)\n\n# Memory ordering support\nT.atomic_add(dst[i, j], value, memory_order=\"relaxed\")\n```\n\n### Example Usage\n\n```python\n@tilelang.jit\ndef atomic_max_kernel(K, M, N, block_M, block_N, dtype=T.float32):\n    @T.prim_func\n    def atomic_max(A: T.Tensor((K, M, N), dtype), B: T.Tensor((M, N), dtype)):\n        with T.Kernel(T.ceildiv(M, block_M), T.ceildiv(N, block_N), K, threads=32) as (bx, by, bz):\n            A_shared = T.alloc_shared((block_M, block_N), dtype)\n            T.copy(A[bz, bx * block_M : (bx + 1) * block_M, by * block_N : (by + 1) * block_N], A_shared)\n            \n            for i, j in T.Parallel(block_M, block_N):\n                T.atomic_max(B[bx * block_M + i, by * block_N + j], A_shared[i, j])\n    return atomic_max\n```\n\n### Vectorization Pass\n\nThe new vectorization pass automatically detects `ForKind::kVectorized` loops containing `atomic_add_elem_op` and converts them to vectorized versions:\n- `float16`/`bfloat16`: Uses `atomic_addx2_elem_op` (2 elements per operation)\n- `float32` on SM>=90: Uses `atomic_addx4_elem_op` (4 elements per operation)\n\n### Architecture Improvements\n\n- Introduced `AtomicOpBaseNode<Derived>` template base class using CRTP pattern\n- Shared implementation for `MakeIterVars`, `MakeIndices`, `MakePredicate`, `MakeSIMTLoop`, `Lower`, and `InferLayout`\n- `AtomicAddNode`, `AtomicMaxNode`, and `AtomicMinNode` all inherit from this base class\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `test_atomic_add` - Basic atomic add\n- [x] `test_atomic_max` - Atomic maximum\n- [x] `test_atomic_min` - Atomic minimum\n- [x] `test_atomic_load_store` - Atomic load/store operations\n- [x] `test_atomic_memory_order` - Memory ordering support\n- [x] `test_atomic_addx2_half` - Vectorized atomic add for float16\n- [x] `test_atomic_addx2_float` - Vectorized atomic add for float32\n- [x] `test_atomic_addx4` - 4-wide vectorized atomic add\n- [x] `test_atomic_return_prev` - Return previous value\n- [x] `test_tile_atomic_add` - Tile-region atomic add\n- [x] `test_tile_atomic_max` - Tile-region atomic max\n- [x] `test_tile_atomic_min` - Tile-region atomic min\n- [x] `test_tma_atomic_add` - TMA-based atomic add\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Tile-level atomic max/min and tensor-region atomic-add with optional return-value and 2x/4x vectorized variants.\n\n* **Vectorization**\n  * Target- and layout-aware vectorization for atomic ops, choosing vector widths based on data type and device capability.\n\n* **Codegen**\n  * CUDA and HIP backends emit the new atomic intrinsics (returning and non-returning variants) and honor optional memory-order hints.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added tests exercising tile-level atomic max, min, and atomic-add paths.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
